Umm at first I thought - wow nice - now I dont have to worrie about falling behind all the hard core players - since I consider myself inbetween the hard core and the casual player..<BR>But then after thinking about it - isent the battle for continues improvement what realy drives most RPG games ? - I know that the vision of SB IS NOT to be like every other game - and its supose to be uniqe !<P>So what happends after 1 month ? - we will have 1000+ level 70th players running around - 10% will continue to level up - with (as I read it) almost NO improvent ! - and the last 90% is left to what ? - guildwars ? - guildevents ? - trade ? - pk'ing - what else ? - I also read a statement saying that equipment wastent a big deal in SB - so no point in adventureing after that... no (almost no) bouns of leveling - so no point in adventureing for exp !<P>I like the idea - at first - but I fear that the game will get "old" to fast ! normaly players look forward to gaining that new level - gettin thoese new sweet skills - spells - hp ... and so on - in SB - whats to look forward to ?<P>Again I know the vision of SB is NOT to be like every other game - but still....<P>Take care<P>Trivan Valliant<BR>Crazy Dane
