<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sounds like you are still an EQ old boy at heart Trivan.  You are correct in your assesment that there will be few people adventuring with their "mains" after about 3 months.  You are corrent in your assesment that equipment will not be vital to your character, hence questing for it is not a necessity.<P>But that is the whole point.  SB is a player driven game, where we are given the reigns and we get to run in any direction we please.  Lets see, what do I want to do today, I can: <P>-Hunt down some of my hated enemies.<BR>-Gather information on the town my guild is planning on seiging next week.<BR>-Slaughter a few monsters to put money in my guild coffers<BR>-Seek out the legendary hero (FC) that has been spotted in the wilds surrounding my city.<BR>-Hunt down some of my hat ... oh I think I said that one already =) Well I will be doing lots of that.<BR>-Travel to and explore another shard, then die and get a free ride home.<BR>-The list goes on and on and on.<P>The type of game you are familiar with, if you played EQ is a game of character development.  The whole point of the game is to build levels and amass gear.  Once your character is all powerfull, or just as powerfull as your time on-line lets you be, you make a twink.  Rinse, repeat, tumble dry low.<P>I think that type of game gets old really fast.  All you do is fight the same mosters with the same AI, over and over again.  AI can only be scripted so well.  A human opponent can always adapt, respond, inovate and generally be a much bigger pain in the butt than a computer opponent.<P>--------------------<P>Certa<BR><A HREF="http://sb.castersrealm.com" TARGET=_blank> <IMG SRC="http://cec.wustl.edu/~dhg1/sbr_banner.gif"> </A><BR>-The pure blood of my ancient elven ancestors courses through my veins, tainted though it may be. One day I will cleanse the taint of humanity from my body, my soul, and then the world.
</FONT>
