<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Yeah, when I played EQ I used to think the EXP grinder was a good thing.  Then I hit level 50, and realized my options for hunting grounds were becoming seriously limited(Considering I hate uber guilds and will NEVER be in one).  So, trust me, the quick leveling is a good thing.  UO didn't have levels, but as far as items went it's almost the same as SB.  Items don't really affect the game, so that means you don't have to go diving into a dungeon if you don't want to.  There are many other things you can do.  I spent most of my time at the guild tower, actually, serving grog and gabbin' away.  SB, there will be more guild wars because there will be something to gain(And a lot to lose, too) from them.  So, we'll have plenty more to do than level!  Wa ha ha ha!    <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
