Well, Leveling up is one thing, getting skills is another, but that is from games of the past!!! <P>As online gameing becomes more and more advanced and closer to Virtual Reality, leveling sounds stupider and stupider. Think about it, in "Real Life" we do not level  up...PRACTICING just makes a person better at what he/she does. (ex Hockey Player) <P>SB seems to be a step towards that. Getting lvl 70,  really is a WARNING saying... "Look, I am LvL 70 I have lots of experience, beware". <P>What it allows is, people that are really good with their skills, have the ability to take down any one in the game. <P>Hey, I play Eq (for a LONG time), I have way more Eq experience than any newbie out there. There are some people in Eq that buy there characters at lvl 60. They have no skill or experience with that character, but, can kill anyone in the game due to there lvl. That is just lame!
