<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
You are looking at this game wrong man.  The end game goal of SB is not to develop your character.  The end game goal of SB is to rule the world or participate in an organization that does.  That means that once leveling your character no longer gives you enough gain for your time you can go out and enhance the power of your guild.  Whether this is by dropping by another guild's favorite dungeon and whiping out a few of them or questing after a legendary runemaster that will enhance your city is up to you.<P>Another tactical thing to remember is the level of your character is a valable statistic in itself.  The further past the soft cap you go the more times you can die before your power starts to decrease substantially.  Now I know everyone is trained by EQ to think that dying is a catastrophic experience that ruins your whole day but I think it is something you will have to get used to in SB.  So say you are level 90 and you are seiging a town.  You die over 20 times but are still almost as powerfull as you were before all those deaths.  Now a level 70 character in the defending guild isn't much weaker than you but she is killed 20 times and is effectively 50th level.  Her power is reduced greatly and she is of less use to the defenders.<P>--------------------<P>Certa<BR><A HREF="http://sb.castersrealm.com" TARGET=_blank> <IMG SRC="http://cec.wustl.edu/~dhg1/sbr_banner.gif"> </A><BR>-The pure blood of my ancient elven ancestors courses through my veins, tainted though it may be. One day I will cleanse the taint of humanity from my body, my soul, and then the world.
